('5320929520C84795962774CA1AE62ADF', 'example', 1, 'A smartphone connected to a vehicle (via USB or Bluetooth) to provide driver navigation on the vehicle''s large screen display'),
('94141E56EA294dfb8212E7FA5553D1F6', 'note', 1, 'The term "top speed" is defined in SAE J3194:2019 in relation to powered micromobility vehicles and is considered to be semantically equivalent to design speed.'),
('CDB8A094578846dcB02F79FBE507F07D', 'note', 1, 'Speed is a function of time.'),
('CDB8A094578846dcB02F79FBE507F07D', 'note', 2, 'Speed is the scalar absolute value (magnitude) of velocity.'),
('E3B6FF9F65A448ffBA3B74876D599814', 'note', 1, 'The abbreviated form ("ADS") is the most preferred form and the alternate form ("Automated Driving System") uses initial capitals to avoid confusion with the more general "driving automation system".'),
('A7CF87D985684eceB59879EF59C87184', 'note', 1, 'The terms "automated vehicle" and "AV" are often used in a colloquial form, however, these terms might be used to mean either an "ADS-equipped vehicle" or a "vehicle with an engaged ADS". The term "ADS-equipped vehicle" is preferred since it is more precise and descriptive in its meaning.'),
('A7CF87D985684eceB59879EF59C87184', 'note', 2, 'The term "autonomous vehicle" is also often used in a colloquial form and is even less well defined. The term is particularly problematic because the word "autonomous" has been used for a long time in the robotics and artificial intelligence research communities to signify systems that have the ability and authority to make decisions independently and self-sufficiently. Due to its imprecise and overly broad meaning, use of the term "autonomous vehicle" is discouraged.'),
('A7CF87D985684eceB59879EF59C87184', 'note', 3, 'This term can, and when possible should be, refined by identifying the level of automation. For example, the terms "level 5 ADS-equipped vehicle" and "level 5 automated vehicle" should be interpreted as "ADS-equipped vehicle where the ADS is a level 5 ADS." '),
('A7CF87D985684eceB59879EF59C87184', 'note', 4, 'This term only describes the capabilities of the vehicle, not its operational state. In other words, the term applies as long as the ADS is connected to the vehicle, whether the DDT is actively engaged or not.'),
('F18A70A730734210891943E1C5F988C3', 'note', 1, 'The malfunction may be internal to the driving automation system or part of another vehicle system.'),
('B67B240E827E493eB1532275FAFAB9BE', 'note', 1, 'Driver support systems include Level 1 and Level 2 driving automation.'),
('65AFD85E052043b0AB87514248666FFA', 'note', 1, 'In contrast to this generic term for any level 1-5 system, the specific term for a level 3-5 system is "Automated Driving System (ADS)." Given the similarity between the generic term, "driving automation system," and the level 3-5-specific term, "Automated Driving System," the latter term is intentionally capitalized when spelled out and reduced to its acronym, "ADS", as much as possible, while "driving automation system" should not be.'),
('65AFD85E052043b0AB87514248666FFA', 'note', 2, 'A driving automation system includes any system capable of level 1-5 driving automation.'),
('65AFD85E052043b0AB87514248666FFA', 'note', 3, 'Driving automation levels are defined in ISO/SAE 22736, which is also known as SAE J3016.'),
('65AFD85E052043b0AB87514248666FFA', 'note', 4, 'Driving automation levels include "level 1 driving automation", "level 2 driving automation", "level 3 ADS", "level 4 ADS", and "level 5 ADS".'),
('53381BA7AB7F48d6AED7DBCA2D07E6C9', 'note', 1, 'The DDT includes lateral vehicle motion control, longitudinal vehicle motion control, monitoring the driving environment, object and event response execution, manoeuvre planning, and enhancing conspicuity.'),
('53381BA7AB7F48d6AED7DBCA2D07E6C9', 'note', 2, 'The DDT excludes strategic functions such as trip scheduling and selection of destinations and waypoints.'),
('ED18EB6F128046bb8904FFA671529FA9', 'note', 1, 'Other driving automation levels include "level 2 driving automation", "level 3 ADS", "level 4 ADS", and "level 5 ADS".'),
('40925DD66C3143bb88BBE7A1C7278FA7', 'note', 1, 'Other driving automation levels include "level 1 driving automation", "level 3 ADS", "level 4 ADS", and "level 5 ADS".'),
('0D13CFB7427A423d9DBC082B91FCEE24', 'note', 1, 'Level 3 ADSs are restricted to operating within a specific ODD.'),
('0D13CFB7427A423d9DBC082B91FCEE24', 'note', 2, 'Other driving automation levels include "level 1 driving automation", "level 2 driving automation", "level 4 ADS", and "level 5 ADS".'),
('0D13CFB7427A423d9DBC082B91FCEE24', 'note', 3, 'The user might need to intervene due to an ADS-issued request, a DDT performance-relevant system failure, or other reasons.'),
('386BE5C5F5924b909CE60CCEC1EA437C', 'note', 1, 'Other driving automation levels include "level 1 driving automation", "level 2 driving automation", "level 3 ADS", and "level 5 ADS".'),
('30D0139B138E427995A7169B36C821FA', 'note', 1, 'Other driving automation levels include "level 1 driving automation", "level 2 driving automation", "level 3 ADS", and "level 4 ADS".'),
('4C8C89A0369D455c9FCE6187A7DD62FC', 'note', 1, 'The conditions might include environmental, geographical, time-of-day, and/or other restrictions.'),
('4C8C89A0369D455c9FCE6187A7DD62FC', 'note', 2, 'The conditions might require the presence or absence of certain traffic or roadway characteristics.'),
('4C8C89A0369D455c9FCE6187A7DD62FC', 'example', 1, 'ADS feature designed to operate a vehicle only on fully access-controlled freeways in low-speed traffic, under fair weather conditions and optimal road maintenance conditions (e.g., good lane markings and not under construction).'),
('4C8C89A0369D455c9FCE6187A7DD62FC', 'example', 2, 'ADS-dedicated vehicle designed to operate only within a geographically-defined area, and only during daylight at speeds not to exceed 25 mph.'),
('ECBC217734464e899D38FA98BFFAA0CA', 'note', 1, 'The vehicle on-board equipment might still be present in the vehicle and might even be partially connected, but not in any operational sense.'),
